/*	
	In update mode, a TDI connector searches the target system for an 
	object that matches the link criteria. If TDI finds a match, it begins
	the modify operation, which maps attributes and call the various modify 
	hooks. When TDI does not find a match, it normally attempts to create a new object
	and selects the add operation. However, when updating RACF-linked ldap servers, TDI
	does not work as designed and throws an exception. The following is a detailed
	explanation of the cause and the procedure implemented to get the proper 
	behavior.

	LDAP connector updZVMsdbm in this AssemblyLine attempts to update the z/VM 
	SDBM LDAP directory, which is actually an interface to RACF. An LDAP search
	directs z/VM to perform the RACF SEARCH command. When the LDAP search is a 
	subtree or one level search and matches no objects, RACF returns an error.
	An example as executed from a distributed platform command line is:
		ldapsearch -h vmsys -D "racfid=itdi,profiletype=user,cn=racfvm" -w passw0rd
			-b "profiletype=user,cn=racfvm" racfid=newuser
	The equivalent RACF command is:
		SEARCH CLASS(USER) FILTER(NEWUSER)
	Assuming newuser does not exist in the VM RACF, the response to both commands is:
		ICH31005I NO ENTRIES MEET SEARCH CRITERIA
	This raises a command error in 
	RACF and creates an unknown error when executed through LDAP, which generates an 
	exception in the TDI. TDI processes 
	that exception here in the "Update Error" hook.

	The link criteria for this connector is "$dn = $($dn), which attempts to match 
	the $dn in the work entry against the $dn of the target LDAP directory. This is 
	a base level search. On a command line it takes this form:
		ldapsearch -h vmsys -D racfid=itdi,profiletype=user,cn=racfvm -w passw0rd
			-b "racfid=newuser,profiletype=user,cn=racfvm" -s base objectclass=*
	The equivalent RACF command is:
		LISTUSER NEWUSER
	RACF returns this error:
		ICH30001I UNABLE TO LOCATE USER    ENTRY NEWUSER 
	In this case LDAP returns a different error code, probably because the LDAP calls
	an underlying routine. The error contains this string:
		Routine 'racf_profileExtractInterface' failed, rc=80 (doListCmdAndSendResults)
	In an update mode operation, TDI sends the LDAP search command to RACF when the lookup
	calls the LDAPConnector.findEntry() method, which throws an exception.

	The code below tests if the exception contains either of the strings that signal a 
	lookup with no results. If found, it calls the LDAPConnector.add() method, which directs
	execution to On Add hooks. Other exceptions lead to the system.skipEntry() method, which
	ensures TDI makes no changes to RACF for this object.
*/
cat("Changenumber '"+work.getString("changenumber")+"' from system '"+work.getString("systemoriginator")+"' to system '"+current_connector+"' synchronization Failed",1);
// cat( "updZVMsdbm.UpdateError: ",2);
gooderror = "ICH31005I NO ENTRIES MEET SEARCH CRITERIA";
gooderror2 = "racf_profileExtractInterface";
if ( error.getString("exception").contains(gooderror) ||
		error.getString("exception").contains(gooderror2) ) {
	thisConnector.getStats().err--;
	error.removeAllAttributes();	
	error.setAttribute("status", "ok");
	thisConnector.add(work);
} else {
//	cat ("updZVMsdbm.UpdateError: This is the error:",2);
//	cat(error,2);
    cat("ITDI0001E : ERROR : logic update sdbm : Sync system aborting",1); 
    task.shutdown();
}

params = thisConnector.getConnectorParam("jndiExtraProviderParams");
//cat("delSdbZVM.BeforeExecute: content of jndiExtraProviderParams is: "+params,2);
position = params.indexOf("connectornumber:")+16;
//cat("delSdbZVM.BeforeExecute: position is : "+position,2);
connectornumber = params.substring(position,position+2);
//cat("delSdbZVM.BeforeExecute: content of connectornumber is: "+connectornumber,2);
current_connector=connectornumber;

cat("delSdbmZVM.BeforeExecute: delSdbmZVM"+current_connector+" and system originator is: zVM" + work.getString("systemoriginator"),2);  
if ( work.getString("systemoriginator").equals(current_connector)) {
     cat("delSdbmZVM.BeforeExecute: delSdbmZVM"+current_connector+" ignored",2);
     system.ignoreEntry();
}

cat("Changenumber '"+work.getString("changenumber")+"' from system '"+work.getString("systemoriginator")+"' to system '"+current_connector+"' synchronization Failed",1);
cat("ITDI0001E : ERROR : logic delSdbmZVM : Sync system aborting",1); 
task.shutdown();

Script.parameter:
/*
	Function cat prints strings or dump objects to the console and/or logs

	LOGDEPTH must be defined globally. Do this in each AssemblyLine Prolog or below.
	It can take any non-negative integer. Zero suppresses all logging. One is the
	ordinary default. Higher values	print objects whose depth equals that value or lower. 

	In the function cat, the default value of the optional argument 'depth' is one (1). 
	Depth can be any positive integer. Higher values suppress printing of the first argument
	unless LOGDEPTH matches or exceeds 'depth'. 

*/


//LOGDEPTH = 1;
function cat ( arg, /* optional argument */ depth ) {
	if (!depth) depth = 1;
	if ( LOGDEPTH >= depth ) {
		try {
			if ( typeof arg == "string" || arg.getClass() == "class java.lang.String" ) {
				task.logmsg( LOGLEVEL, arg );
			} else {
				task.dump( arg );
			}
		} catch (e) {
			task.dump( arg );  // dump() calls dumpEntry() for TDI entry objects
		}
	}
}

